# Learning Reflection
During this project I learned that Git is much more than a backup tool.

Git records the complete history of a software project and allows developers to safely experiment with new features while maintaining the ability to return to previous working versions.

I also learned that creating small, meaningful commits after completing milestones makes debugging easier and provides a clear record of project progress.

Git is an essential software engineering tool and is considered a standard skill for professional software developers.
